</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I play a dark elf on the PvP server, and have since phase 4. I somewhat feared that the server might become what you descibed, but in reality it's nothing like that. As far as the dark elves go, we police our own kind. I only heard of one or two players pking other dark elves, and a warning was shouted about these bad apples. I did see people pking other dark elves if one looted a corpse that wasn't his/hers, but thats just called policing (-: I would do the same thing.

<P>I don't know about the other races though, so I can only tell you about the dark elves. Though the dark elves are the only race that matters (-:
<P>- Ceyana
<P>&gt; I just have some general concerns about the PvP server, and I
<BR>&gt; was hoping that someone here might be able to shed a little
<BR>&gt; light on some stuff for me.
<P>&gt; I am getting ready to start my "main" EQ character,
<BR>&gt; and I am really wanting to do it on the PvP server...but, my
<BR>&gt; concern is the Roleplaying aspect...from my past experiences,
<BR>&gt; anytime there was PvP, it ends up just being a bunch of people
<BR>&gt; running around killing each other screaming "How'd that
<BR>&gt; feel Beotch! EvIl DaWgZ in Da Howse!!!"...this is EXACTLY
<BR>&gt; what I DO NOT WANT...So, my question is...is it like that on the
<BR>&gt; PvP server? I mean I know you will ALWAYS have idiots like this,
<BR>&gt; but for the most part what is it like? Are there lots of
<BR>&gt; Roleplayers? Or is it just mass chaos? Im picturing the UO AByss
<BR>&gt; server only worse (and thats scarey!)
<P>&gt; Please respond...thanks!
<BR>
